- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computational geometry, the study of graph parameters and algorithmic results on graphs can be considered as a subfield of computational geometry. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper does not directly relate to game theory, but the study of graph parameters and algorithmic results on graphs can be applied to game theory problems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper does not focus on computational complexity, but the study of algorithmic results on graphs can be related to computational complexity.
